2026-04-21 02:48:41 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 1', 'Control Module 2', 'Control Module 3', 'Control Module 4', 'Control Module 5', 'Control Module 6', 'Control Module 7', 'Control Module 8'] hypothesis_explanation="All the control module switch indicator LEDs (and presumably their series resistors) have been removed, resulting in an open circuit in each control module. Since the LEDs form the only current path between the input and output in each module (with switch 'on'), removal of the LED effectively breaks the circuit, preventing current from reaching the load. This explains why the lamp does not light and the control module LEDs do not light. The power supply LED still works as it is in parallel with the battery and has not been disturbed. Restoring complete current paths in all control modules by replacing missing LEDs will restore system operation."
